{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Buchheit and Laursen (2013) demonstrated that the RPE (Borg Scale) has shown a great correlation with HR, ventilation, and VO 2 in individuals with and without CAD, and the correlation is not impacted by beta-blocker medication, a commonly used HR modulating medication by patients with CAD.",
    "Participants' heart rate was recorded using Polar heart rate monitors minute to minute of exercise.",
    "The control group did not receive any additional follow-up regarding exercise beyond general advice on the importance of exercise and diet.",
    "Each training session was initiated with a 5-10-min warm-up at 50-60% HRpeak and ended with 5 min of cooldown at 40% HRpeak.",
    "The HIIT group performed 4 × 4-min high-intensity intervals at 85-95% HRpeak followed by a 1-min recovery interval at 40% HRpeak, predicted with a supervised graded exercise test on a treadmill with the Bruce protocol (Bires et al. 2013)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Buchheit and Laursen (2013) demonstrated that the RPE (Borg Scale) has shown a great correlation with HR, ventilation, and VO 2 in individuals with and without CAD, and the correlation is not impacted by beta-blocker medication, a commonly used HR modulating medication by patients with CAD.",
    "The HIIT group performed 4 × 4-min high-intensity intervals at 85-95% HRpeak followed by a 1-min recovery interval at 40% HRpeak, predicted with a supervised graded exercise test on a treadmill with the Bruce protocol (Bires et al. 2013)."
